109
0:04:51.573,000 --> 0:04:53,000
DNA is about two nanometers across, which is really quite tiny.

110
0:04:54.572,000 --> 0:04:55,000
But in each one of your cells,

111
0:04:56.03,000 --> 0:04:59,000
each strand of DNA is about 30 to 40 million nanometers long.

112
0:04:59.674,000 --> 0:05:02,000
So to keep the DNA organized and regulate access to the genetic code,

113
0:05:03.514,000 --> 0:05:05,000
it's wrapped around these purple proteins --

114
0:05:05.621,000 --> 0:05:06,000
or I've labeled them purple here.

115
0:05:07.227,000 --> 0:05:08,000
It's packaged up and bundled up.

116
0:05:08.835,000 --> 0:05:1,000
All this field of view is a single strand of DNA.

117
0:05:11.771,000 --> 0:05:14,000
